chart_description: This chart represents the percentage of memory full pressure on the system. Memory full pressure refers to the amount of memory available to the system as it nears its limit.

dimension_descriptions.full 10: The percentage of memory full pressure when there is 10% memory left.
dimension_descriptions.full 300: The percentage of memory full pressure when there is 300% memory left.
dimension_descriptions.full 60: The percentage of memory full pressure when there is 60% memory left.
